  "blogs": [
    {
      "id": "blog-1",
      "title": "Why A2 Cow Milk is Better for Your Digestive System",
      "summary": "Discover the health differences between A1 and A2 proteins and how switching to A2 milk can alleviate bloating and discomfort.",
      "content": "A2 Cow Milk is milk that contains only the A2 type of beta-casein protein, rather than the more common A1 protein found in regular store-bought milk. For decades, traditional Indian breeds of cows (like Gir, Sahiwal, and Ongole) have naturally produced 100% A2 milk. Recent research demonstrates that A2 beta-casein is processed differently by our digestive enzymes, preventing the release of BCM-7 (Beta-casomorphin-7), which has been linked to bloating, stomach cramps, and inflammatory reactions. Swapping your daily milk for Reddy Premium A2 Cow Milk ensures not only pure farm-fresh flavor but also comfortable digestion and superior calcium absorption.",
      "category": "Health Articles",
      "image": "/images/cow_milk.png",
      "readTime": "4 min read",
      "date": "2026-07-01"
    },
    {
      "id": "blog-2",
      "title": "Perfect Soft Paneer Tikka Recipe for Family Evenings",
      "summary": "An easy step-by-step recipe to get restaurant-style soft Paneer Tikka using Reddy Fresh Malai Paneer at home.",
      "content": "To prepare perfect soft Paneer Tikka, the secret lies in the moisture of the Paneer and the consistency of the marinade. Step 1: Take 200g of Reddy Fresh Malai Paneer and cut into thick cubes. Step 2: Soak the cubes in lukewarm water for 10 minutes, then pat dry. Step 3: Mix hung curd with mustard oil, Kashmiri red chilli powder, ginger-garlic paste, garam masala, and kasuri methi. Step 4: Gently fold the paneer cubes, diced onions, and bell peppers into the paste. Step 5: Roast in a hot oven or grill pan for 12-15 minutes until charred at the edges. Garnish with lemon juice and serve with mint chutney!",
      "category": "Recipes",
      "image": "/images/paneer.png",
      "readTime": "5 min read",
      "date": "2026-06-28"
    }
  ],
